I have tried doing everything but still cant get the input function working.
Though some of my investigation on the issue should be useful

1. Service worker is correctly in place and is forwarding message
2. PythonProvider is also fine as `REACT_PY_AWAITING_INPUT` is successfully caught and `setWorkerAwaitingInputIds` , `setWorkerAwaitingInputPrompt` is running as expected.( Assuming that the ids and prompt is also setup currently)
3. There is no change is `workerAwaitingInputIds` in `usePython` and I assume that this is the place whole chain breaks.

Methodology to test the previously mentioned points.

1. Bunch of `console.log()` to check every step where the Input is related.
2. Using of useEffect to determine if `workerAwaitingInputIds` is changed or not (which Failed).

Tested version for the issue: 1.10.7 to 1.9

The nextJs page code
```js
'use client'
import { useState,useEffect } from 'react'
import { PythonProvider, usePython } from '../../react-py/src'


const Page = () => {
  const [code, setCode] = useState('input("hello:")')
  const {interruptExecution,isAwaitingInput,isLoading,isReady,isRunning,prompt,runPython,sendInput,stderr,stdout}=usePython()

  useEffect(() => {
    navigator.serviceWorker
      .register('/service-worker.js')
      .then((registration) =>
        console.log(
          'Service Worker registration successful with scope: ',
          registration.scope
        )
      )
      .catch((err) => console.log('Service Worker registration failed: ', err))
  }, [])


  return (
    <PythonProvider lazy={true}>
      {isAwaitingInput && <p>INPUT A</p>}
      {isLoading && <p>Loading A</p>}
      {isReady && <p>READY A</p>}
      {isRunning && <p>RUNNING A</p>}
      <input type="text" value={code} onChange={e=>setCode(e.target.value)}/>
      <button onClick={e=>{runPython(code)}}>RUN</button>
      <button onClick={e=>{sendInput('sdfghj')}}>SEND INPUT</button>
      <button onClick={e=>{interruptExecution()}}>INTERUPT</button>
      <p>{stdout}</p>
    </PythonProvider>
  )
}

export default Page

```

NOTE: using `sendInput()` anyway also doesn't work

